Script_exp_2.js file:

function create() {
let num = document.getElementById("table").value;
let arr = [];

for (let i = 1; i <= 10; i++) {
arr.push(`${num} X ${i} = ${num * i}`);
}

for (let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
document.getElementById("result").innerHTML += ` ${arr[i]}<br>`;
}
}











Algorithm :-
1. Enter the number for which the table is to be generated.
2. Write logic for table creation using one of the following :
   a. for loop
   b. whil eloop
3. Display entire table as 
   2 x 1 = 2
   2 x 2 = 4
   and so on...
4. Stop
